Source: Ohio Department of Health [edited]
<http://www.odh.state.oh.us/alerts/sbass/sbupdate.asp>

Alerts & Advisories: Information about South Bass Island Outbreak
--------------------------------------------------
As of Thu, 2 Sep 2004, the Ottawa County Health Department received reports
of 1426 people who have a history of gastrointestinal illness and travel to
South Bass Island.
To help protect both residents of and visitors to South Bass Island, the
Ohio Department of Health urges residents with wells to consider vigorously
boiling their water for 1 minute before drinking, cooking, making prepared
drinks or brushing teeth. Visitors to South Bass Island are urged to
consider drinking only bottled water.
Visitors from 17 states, a European country and a Canadian province have
reported illness. These cases involve illness in travelers to South Bass
from out of town.
--
