Date: Sat, 28 Aug 2004
From: Brent Barrett <salbrent46143@yahoo.com>

Has anyone checked the ice consumed on the boats and island? Ice holding
areas and ice machines can become contaminated or an improper machine drain
tube can cause problems. Commerical-type ice tea brewers have also been
found contaminated with coliforms.
--
Brent Barrett
Indiana State Dept of Health
Indianapolis, IN
<salbrent46143@yahoo.com>
[The number of reported symptomatic individuals continues to grow; new
cases appear to be continuing. Contaminated water certainly appears to be
involved, and how so many wells became contaminated is not yet clear.
Dr. Barrett's point regarding ice is worthwhile considering in the mix. -
Mod.LL]
